14:27.720 --> 14:34.440
Ladies and gentlemen, friends of Tennessee, let me pause today and lay aside the issues

14:34.440 --> 14:40.920
and the problems of the Senate for a moment. This is a season when hundreds of our young people

14:40.920 --> 14:48.360
in Tennessee and all over the nation are leaving behind them the golden days of high school or of

14:48.360 --> 14:57.000
college. This is the time when the dreams of youth must be translated at last into the accomplishments

14:57.000 --> 15:05.800
of life. This is the time when a parent sees in the shining face of his child that this young one

15:05.800 --> 15:14.760
is no longer really a child, but a man or a woman now facing the challenge of a vigorous and competitive

15:14.760 --> 15:22.120
world. Out of the dreams of young men and women come their raw materials for building a life

15:22.840 --> 15:30.920
with meaning and with substance. This is your challenge. It is a challenge of many faces.

15:32.120 --> 15:38.840
You will see it in the hand of a small child someday when it reaches to you for strength and guidance.

15:40.200 --> 15:46.920
You will see it in the hard holes of commerce. Hear it in the courts of law and find it across

15:46.920 --> 15:55.320
the bargaining table. You will see it in your church and your civic club and perhaps even reach it

15:55.320 --> 16:01.400
in the empty void of space on the way to the moon before your life time has run its course.

