19:05.080 --> 19:17.160
Ladies and gentlemen, friends of Tennessee, as I make this broadcast year for Washington,

19:17.160 --> 19:22.040
the United States Senate is still debating the appointment of Lewis L. Strauss to the

19:22.040 --> 19:28.040
Post of Secretary of Commerce. Earlier this week, I delivered a lengthy address on this issue

19:28.040 --> 19:34.280
on the floor of the Senate. My task was not a happy one. I was compelled to put aside my natural

19:34.280 --> 19:39.160
inclination to support the President of the United States and the executive nomination.

19:39.960 --> 19:45.240
My sincerity in saying this is borne out by the fact that in the last six and a half years of

19:45.240 --> 19:50.040
this administration, many thousands, hundreds of thousands of executive nominations,

19:50.760 --> 19:55.720
which have come before the Senate, I have supported all but a very few, three I believe.

19:56.360 --> 20:00.200
And I believe that history has supported the stand I took in those instances.

20:01.160 --> 20:05.880
Those who have been pushing the confirmation of Mr. Strauss have sought to divert attention from

20:05.880 --> 20:13.640
the real issue. The issue is not simply public power versus private power. It is not presidential prestige.

20:14.280 --> 20:18.600
It is not the patriotism of one man as compared to the patriotism of other men.

20:19.160 --> 20:23.800
Nor is it by any, by the wildest stretch of the imagination and issue of religion.

20:24.520 --> 20:30.520
The true issue is, in my opinion, that Louis L Strauss is unfit to hold the important

20:30.520 --> 20:36.520
post of Secretary of Commerce, because he has consistently and cynically sought to deceive

20:36.520 --> 20:42.840
the American people. I experienced this trait in Mr. Strauss at first hand during the lengthy

20:42.840 --> 20:50.360
hearings on the notorious Dixonates contract. The facts developed in the antitrust subcommittee hearings

20:50.360 --> 20:56.200
revealed a disgraceful attempt by the big finance and power interest to destroy the Tennessee

20:56.200 --> 21:03.400
Valley Authority. These facts pointed a finger directly at Louis L Strauss. He could not have failed

21:03.400 --> 21:09.000
to know of the conflict of interest, which finally led to the cancellation of the Dixonates contract.

21:09.960 --> 21:14.200
When Mr. Strauss came before the interstate and foreign commerce committee recently,

21:14.760 --> 21:21.240
these facts were brought out again, and again Mr. Strauss sought to twist out from under them.

21:21.800 --> 21:27.480
He implied half-truths and misstatements. The senators on this committee who voted unfavorably

21:27.480 --> 21:33.560
on reporting his confirmation cited seven specific instances in which Louis L Strauss

21:34.200 --> 21:39.400
sought to deceive the committee in the course of the very hearings on his fitness to hold the

21:39.400 --> 21:45.960
post of Secretary of Commerce. These are the seven findings of the senators. One, he flatly

21:45.960 --> 21:51.960
misrepresented to the committee his responsibility for rejecting an application for a license to

21:51.960 --> 21:58.280
export steel pipe. Second, he falsely denied making its statement for a subcommittee of the House

21:58.280 --> 22:04.200
appropriations committee. Three, he distorted the nature of a charge brought against him by Senator

22:04.360 --> 22:11.240
Anderson concerning the export of ISIL tones. Fourth, in dealing with charges that he had failed to

22:11.240 --> 22:17.480
keep the joint committee on atomic energy properly informed, Louis Strauss sought to distort the record.

22:18.360 --> 22:24.920
And fifth, Louis L Strauss denied knowledge of the conflict of interest in the Dixonates contract

22:24.920 --> 22:31.000
and attempted to hide it. And I will have more to say about this later if I have time.

22:31.800 --> 22:37.960
And six, he falsely sought to create the impression that he had no connection with the ill-advised

22:37.960 --> 22:44.600
actions of the AEC. Seven, he denied that he had ever sought material against a hostile witness

22:45.240 --> 22:50.280
and was later confronted with an official letter showing that he had sought and received this

22:50.280 --> 22:57.480
material. Well, against this most recent backdrop of deception, the long record of hearings and

22:57.480 --> 23:05.400
innovations in the Dixonates Yates case stand out in starking clarity today. The chain of events

23:05.400 --> 23:11.480
shows beyond the shadow of a doubt that Louis L Strauss must have known of the conflict of interest

23:12.040 --> 23:17.640
that infected the entire Dixonates deal from its very beginning, which the Department of Justice

23:17.640 --> 23:23.640
of Justice now conceives. Everyone around him and their atomic energy commission and the Bureau

23:23.720 --> 23:30.040
of the Budget knew of it. It could not escape to him. When I placed this chain of facts alongside

23:30.040 --> 23:36.200
the half facts and misstatements charged to Louis L Strauss by the Senators of the Interstate and

23:36.200 --> 23:42.520
Foreign Commerce Committee who opposed his nomination, I could come to only one honest conclusion.

23:43.160 --> 23:49.640
My conclusion was that Louis L Strauss has continually sought to deceive the American people.

23:49.720 --> 23:54.680
In the face of this overwhelming proof, I simply cannot vote for his confirmation. Thank you

23:54.680 --> 23:56.680
and that's all for this time.

